x4freetext: Up to six GeLi and HPGe detectors in
different geometries were used to minimize systematic
Two stacks consisting of uranium foils in
natural isotopic composition separated by high-purity
copper foils for flux monitoring.  The 70-MeV stack
also contained some aluminum targets for cross checking
The stacks were irradiated for about 7.74 and
4.98 hours, respectively, at initial proton energies of
After irradiation each foil was subsequently

up to 6 months after irradiation by means of
The initially produced activity of every

uncertainties from all known sources of uncertainty
